1
00:00:11,170 --> 00:00:15,920
What... is this picture?

2
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:23,330
This is why I don't like people touching my things.

3
00:00:23,330 --> 00:00:25,500
Wait.

4
00:00:31,710 --> 00:00:42,390
Was I, by any chance, Kim Ian's girlfriend or dating him?

5
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:52,260
Why are you asking me? I wouldn't know.

6
00:00:53,250 --> 00:00:59,600
Why are you being so curt? I'm in the picture with Kim Ian. It's like...

7
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,860
Like what?

8
00:01:06,940 --> 00:01:11,530
Did you know who I was from the start?

9
00:01:11,530 --> 00:01:15,480
So, you had this picture.

10
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:23,770
You knew that I was close enough with Kim Ian to be friends.

11
00:01:23,770 --> 00:01:25,790
No?

12
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:32,500
I just saw this picture for the first time, too. Whether you believe me or not.

13
00:01:32,500 --> 00:01:34,270
What did you say?

14
00:01:34,270 --> 00:01:38,980
The sheet music with this picture was written on by my brother.

15
00:01:38,980 --> 00:01:45,510
I don't know how to explain it, but things like this kept happening to me in the past year.

16
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:01,530
Look at this.

17
00:02:01,530 --> 00:02:05,130
Ian was obsessed with taking pictures at that time.

18
00:02:05,130 --> 00:02:12,320
He loved people so much. After his death, these things popped up all over the house.

19
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:17,890
From a book, from a bag. Even from this sheet music.

20
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:24,300
That's when I hid them together, because I couldn't bear to look at them.

21
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:28,690
I see.

22
00:02:34,940 --> 00:02:40,350
We looked happy. Though I don't remember.

23
00:02:42,010 --> 00:02:46,050
I wonder who Kim Ian was to me.

24
00:02:49,270 --> 00:02:51,690
I hope he was a good memory.

25
00:02:51,690 --> 00:02:57,070
That way, I'll feel less sorry to you and your brother.

26
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:04,460
No. You don't have to feel sorry towards me.

27
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:06,430
Wait.

28
00:03:07,540 --> 00:03:11,570
Can I take this picture?

29
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:16,000
Sure. Do that.

30
00:03:27,730 --> 00:03:30,250
How could someone always be hungry?

31
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:35,210
Now that I think of it, I haven't eaten since lunch.

32
00:03:35,210 --> 00:03:41,330
Yun. Can I ask you something? I've wanted to know for a while.

33
00:03:41,330 --> 00:03:42,980
What is it?

34
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:49,510
If Kim Ian is your biological younger brother, why are your last names different?

35
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,820
Oh.

36
00:03:55,050 --> 00:04:02,710
When I was ten, my mom took my brother and left. After that, he took my mother's last name.

37
00:04:03,670 --> 00:04:06,690
At ten?

38
00:04:06,690 --> 00:04:10,200
Why didn't you follow your mom?

39
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:13,130
Because that's the way my mom wanted it..

40
00:04:14,220 --> 00:04:19,900
Remember when you said that you were alone in this world?

41
00:04:22,260 --> 00:04:24,940
I'm like that, too. I'm also alone.

42
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:29,470
My father was always busy so I never saw his face.

43
00:04:29,470 --> 00:04:33,220
Even during my middle school admission.

44
00:04:33,220 --> 00:04:38,740
And at my graduation, I was alone.

45
00:04:38,740 --> 00:04:45,670
My mother left,  My brother died, my father and I broke off relations.

46
00:04:45,670 --> 00:04:49,600
And then next, well, as you see, I'm  living a tough life,

47
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:53,280
and on a rainy day I met you in front of this convenience store.

48
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:58,250
- Yun.
- Yeah?

49
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,080
What's that?

50
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:05,540
Why do you say stuff like that while smiling? It's sad.

51
00:05:05,540 --> 00:05:12,000
I at least had a big family, but you literally had no one.

52
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:15,670
When you were only ten.

53
00:05:18,340 --> 00:05:20,930
Aigoo!

54
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:34,780
I just saw this picture for the first time, too. Whether you believe me or not.

55
00:05:34,780 --> 00:05:38,420
Is what he said true? What's for sure is,

56
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:44,300
in my missing three months, there is Kim Ian, and he is related to me.

57
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:52,850
- Who killed your brother?
- Someone he loved.

58
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:56,920
Who was the person Kim Ian loved?

59
00:06:00,890 --> 00:06:06,460
And... why did I take such a picture with him?

60
00:06:06,460 --> 00:06:09,310
I want to know more about him.

61
00:06:15,420 --> 00:06:19,020
Kim Su In, Chopin Concerto No.

62
00:06:19,020 --> 00:06:23,260
- Why didn't you follow your mom?
- I didn't know my mother's face.

63
00:06:23,260 --> 00:06:26,900
Why do you say stuff like that while smiling? It's sad.

64
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:32,590
I at least had a big family, but you literally had no one..

65
00:06:32,590 --> 00:06:36,110
When you were only ten.

66
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:44,260
I Wanna Hear Your Song

67
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:47,550
Good morning!

68
00:06:47,550 --> 00:06:53,720
The conductor issued the parts for the different instruments.  I'll distribute it.  Please look at it before  today's practice.

69
00:06:54,780 --> 00:06:58,460
Ugh, again?

70
00:06:58,460 --> 00:07:00,040
Why is Maestro Nam like this?

71
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:03,610
- So annoying.
- What is this?

72
00:07:03,610 --> 00:07:05,090
A 15 degree angle?

73
00:07:05,090 --> 00:07:09,190
Now, he's even setting the bowing angle? He's really driving me crazy.

74
00:07:09,190 --> 00:07:11,920
Good luck.

75
00:07:13,060 --> 00:07:16,560
You and I, we're both working hard.

76
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:23,200
Oh, who is this?

77
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,110
Did you find this?

78
00:07:27,110 --> 00:07:30,780
Yeah.  It's been a while.  When I was in middle school, I listened to this CD.

79
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:36,820
Wow. Seeing this sunbae reminds me of my past. I worked with her before.

80
00:07:36,820 --> 00:07:38,910
You performed with her?

81
00:07:38,910 --> 00:07:44,580
It  wasn't performing together.  When I was barely okay, I entered the orchestra. She was the guest collaborator.

82
00:07:44,580 --> 00:07:49,970
This sunbae's Chopin was amazing.  When she got married and retired shortly after, everyone was sad.

83
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:54,640
- How was she?
- A beauty with talent, who was fussy.

84
00:07:54,640 --> 00:08:00,120
She was a star in those times. But after her marriage, she had a string of misfortunes.

85
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:04,980
She divorced, then her son died in an accident. You should  know about it, too.

86
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:08,500
His name was Kim Ian. He performed with the Asia Philharmonic last year.

87
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:15,720
- What?
- I guess you didn't know. Well, there were only hushed whispers.

88
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:18,750
But there was a scary rumor back then as well.

89
00:08:18,750 --> 00:08:21,820
- Scary rumor?
- Yeah.

90
00:08:23,770 --> 00:08:28,870
- The rumor that his father killed him.
- What?

91
00:08:41,540 --> 00:08:44,770
Su-In Kim
Chopin Piano Concerto No.1 & 4 Ballades

92
00:08:47,330 --> 00:08:52,900
From the start there was  talk about how Kim Ian was born as a bastard child.

93
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:59,010
When Kim Ian died last year, the father didn't even get a message and there was no article about it, not even a line.

94
00:08:59,010 --> 00:09:02,390
After that, his father tried to enact revenge on his wife,

95
00:09:02,390 --> 00:09:06,580
and rumors spread that he killed her under the disguise of a car accident.

96
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:14,140
She was my favorite pianist when I was young. She's Yun's mother?

97
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:20,600
I wonder if he also knows about the scary rumor.

98
00:09:22,170 --> 00:09:29,770
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

99
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:42,410
I didn't know how to contact you so I came personally.

100
00:09:42,410 --> 00:09:47,000
- Does your cousin know you're here?
- Do you want her to know? Let's talk for a minute.

101
00:09:52,930 --> 00:09:58,860
I'll get right to the point. I want to know why you keep hanging around Yi Yeong.

102
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:03,610
We're only getting close. Does there have to be a reason?

103
00:10:03,610 --> 00:10:09,020
We lived in the same neighborhood so we met a few times, and that naturally turned into friendship.

104
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:17,570
Don't say nonsense. I know you approached her on purpose. I heard you said you're Kim Ian's older brother. Is that still coincidence?

105
00:10:17,570 --> 00:10:20,720
Why is it a problem that I'm Kim Ian's brother?

106
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:26,820
I'm more curious, as to why you came all this way to see me. May I ask why?

107
00:10:26,820 --> 00:10:31,780
You know my brother died in a car accident one year ago, right? Next to him on that day was Hong Yi Yeong.

108
00:10:31,780 --> 00:10:34,730
You must have known, right? That Hong Yi Yeong and my brother were together that day.

109
00:10:34,730 --> 00:10:41,030
What are you saying? Yi Yeong was found on a different day, time and place than your brother.

110
00:10:41,030 --> 00:10:44,370
The police don't even know if they were together.

111
00:10:44,370 --> 00:10:51,310
It's a one-day difference. Hong Yi Yeong's bag was discovered in his car. Didn't you receive it from the police?

112
00:10:51,310 --> 00:10:53,560
I don't know what you're trying to say. I don't know anything.

113
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:58,940
- There was a stab wound in Ian's body. Did you know that?
- How could I?

114
00:10:58,940 --> 00:11:05,330
Then why did you come to see me? Why do you care why I'm friends with Hong Yi Yeong? What are you scared of?

115
00:11:05,330 --> 00:11:08,960
My brother is dead and Hong Yi Yeong is alive with memory loss.

116
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:13,390
The only person who witnessed everything that night was Hong Yi Yeong.

117
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:26,930
You're a psychiatrist, so you probably led sessions with her.

118
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:31,840
Do you think she might have killed my brother?

119
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:38,540
Are you afraid of Hong Yi Yeong regaining her memory? In case she's a murderer who killed somone?

120
00:11:42,530 --> 00:11:46,140
I don't know why you're like this, but stay away from Yi Yeong.

121
00:11:46,140 --> 00:11:53,380
If I see you around her, I won't stay still. I'm warning you. I'm different ftom Yi Yeong.

122
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:20,170
Sir? Sir?

123
00:12:32,180 --> 00:12:37,870
- You got scared.
- You scared me!

124
00:12:44,230 --> 00:12:47,710
- Should we got get some fresh air?
- Right now?

125
00:12:47,710 --> 00:12:53,790
Yeah. I think my head will explode from looking at this music.

126
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:07,570
Why did you record the rehearsal?

127
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:15,910
I didn't want to just stand there. If I post it on our social media, the fans will like it, too.

128
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:18,700
- Sir?
- Yes?

129
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:26,340
You said you performed with Kim Ian when you were in the Asia Philharmonic, right? Were you perhaps friends with him?

130
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:28,810
Why?

131
00:13:28,810 --> 00:13:33,650
I just wanted to what kind of person he was.

132
00:13:38,770 --> 00:13:41,880
Why so suddenly?

133
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:45,780
Oh. There's no big reason.

134
00:13:45,780 --> 00:13:53,230
A few days ago, when we were at Conductor Song's place, I  asked you about the poster we saw, right?

135
00:13:53,230 --> 00:13:57,580
This person, Kim Ian. Do you know him?

136
00:13:57,580 --> 00:14:01,390
Oh, I thought you meant someone special. You really don't know?

137
00:14:01,390 --> 00:14:03,600
Truthfully,

138
00:14:04,990 --> 00:14:09,850
at that time, I asked because I really didn't know.

139
00:14:11,330 --> 00:14:16,520
- Did you know I was in an accident last year? With a taxi.
- Yeah.

140
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:22,910
- At Conductor Song's house, did you say it was on your way to a concert?

141
00:14:22,910 --> 00:14:28,390
Yes.  I'm confessing it now, but I actually lost my memories from before that incident.

142
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:34,190
But recently, I happened to learn that I also lost memories of Kim Ian.

143
00:14:34,190 --> 00:14:37,840
You happened to learn? How?

144
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:41,790
Oh. That is...

145
00:14:41,790 --> 00:14:45,870
I mean, um...

146
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:49,440
I coincidentally saw a picture I had taken with Kim Ian.

147
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:57,750
We looked very close, but I have no memory of him at all. It's no big deal, so you can forget about it.

148
00:14:59,280 --> 00:15:03,650
He was a good person. Kim Ian.

149
00:15:03,650 --> 00:15:09,800
He liked people, smiled a lot, and he was a musical genius.

150
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:12,520
I see.

151
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:17,840
Someone like that died.

152
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:30,490
Here.

153
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:44,550
Sit. Tell them to bring another order of the same thing.

154
00:15:44,550 --> 00:15:48,660
I work here part-time, so I can't sit.

155
00:15:48,660 --> 00:15:54,630
I'm the CEO here. I'm the owner. Sit.

156
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:07,870
I'll bring another bottle of wine for you to drink.

157
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:17,580
I'm not talking long.  Get out of the Sinyeong Philharmonic immediately and go to the US. Go and complete your studies.

158
00:16:17,580 --> 00:16:23,360
What's the point of studying.  You don't know it but I really am done with school.

159
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:28,190
I can't not show up at work even if I want to.  It's how I make a living.

160
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:35,180
Do you think I would've come here if I had other options?

161
00:16:36,190 --> 00:16:41,420
Stop worrying about Ian. Leave Hong Yi Yeong alone, too. Stop looking for answers.

162
00:16:41,420 --> 00:16:44,430
Is something bothering you?

163
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:50,050
I continue to worry about you.

164
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:52,850
Please stop lying.

165
00:16:52,850 --> 00:16:58,300
You're worrying about  someone else? Even a stray dog would laugh.

166
00:16:58,300 --> 00:17:03,150
Your son's organs were all ruptured, and you prevented an autopsy and had him cremated.

167
00:17:03,150 --> 00:17:08,590
You even sent him off without a proper funeral. Stopped the police from investigating, too. Why are you doing this?

168
00:17:08,590 --> 00:17:12,950
Crazy bastard. I won't tell you a second time.

169
00:17:12,950 --> 00:17:17,820
Distinguish yourself at the Sinyeong Philharmonic. It won't mean a thing to me.

170
00:17:18,990 --> 00:17:24,970
Is the rumor true? The one that says you killed Ian?

171
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:35,700
What's going to happen if I find out who killed Ian and why? Are you going to kill me, too?

172
00:17:37,150 --> 00:17:43,290
If I say I'll kill you, will you stop? Then I'll kill you.

173
00:17:50,490 --> 00:17:54,490
Should we talk about the recurring dreams you've been having?

174
00:17:54,490 --> 00:18:01,900
It's because I'm worried that you haven't been sleeping easily. Just comfortably say what you remember.

175
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:07,730
Anything's okay, since it's a dream. Did you have the same dream yesterday?

176
00:18:07,730 --> 00:18:13,100
Yes. I was running away to somewhere.

177
00:18:13,100 --> 00:18:17,790
There weren't many cars on the dark road.

178
00:18:17,790 --> 00:18:23,960
There was so much rain, I couldn't see properly.

179
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:29,210
There was a knife in my hand.

180
00:18:29,210 --> 00:18:33,500
Knife? What kind of knife?

181
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:41,350
The one that comes out a lot in movies. A switchblade knife.

182
00:18:41,350 --> 00:18:43,680
But...

183
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:48,300
the blood on my hands.

184
00:18:51,580 --> 00:18:54,780
There was blood

185
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:01,100
on my hands.

186
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:09,410
Deleting files

187
00:19:12,070 --> 00:19:15,930
Would you like to delete this folder?

188
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:27,500
A blind date? Not Unni, but me?

189
00:19:27,510 --> 00:19:30,550
Don't mention her.

190
00:19:30,550 --> 00:19:33,590
I told her to go on a date to have a look, and my pride crashed.

191
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:41,100
Hey. Would you like to see him first? Here.

192
00:19:44,230 --> 00:19:46,060
He's decent.

193
00:19:46,060 --> 00:19:49,330
Jeez. A person's personality is suddenly...

194
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:52,400
- What's with you?
- Let her go see for herself.

195
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:55,870
Whatever. She could.

196
00:19:55,870 --> 00:20:00,950
Aunt.  Can't you hold of on the arranged dates. I'm still not a member of the orchestra.

197
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:07,300
Don't say anything. Take your time on the weekend. If you don't, I'll remove you from the family register.

198
00:20:11,750 --> 00:20:13,930
I'm home!

199
00:20:13,930 --> 00:20:15,550
Welcome home.

200
00:20:15,550 --> 00:20:17,830
I could just die.

201
00:20:17,830 --> 00:20:20,880
The consultation went overtime.

202
00:20:20,900 --> 00:20:25,900
Look at that. The doctor didn't even wash. Go wash up.

203
00:20:25,990 --> 00:20:30,060
Mom, I'm tired. Let me stay for just a minute.

204
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:32,760
Got it.

205
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:36,260
They'll take away your doctor's license.

206
00:20:36,260 --> 00:20:38,760
Here. Eat this.

207
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:40,420
Sure.

208
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:43,430
- Oh, Unni!
- What is it?

209
00:20:43,430 --> 00:20:48,880
Do you happen to know exactly where I had the taxi accident last year?

210
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:51,230
Why are you asking so out of the blue?

211
00:20:51,230 --> 00:20:55,350
I thought you said it was somewhere in Yongin. But I don't think so.

212
00:20:55,350 --> 00:20:59,730
The last time I went with Jang Yun, I saw a place which looked familiar.

213
00:20:59,730 --> 00:21:03,130
Where did you go with Jang Yun?

214
00:21:03,130 --> 00:21:04,240
Near Gapyeong.

215
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:07,410
Near Gapyeong?  Where in Gapyeong?

216
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:11,890
Are you stupid?

217
00:21:11,890 --> 00:21:15,400
It's not once or twice.  Why are you being dragged here and there by a neighborhood guy?

218
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:17,770
I wasn't dragged. I said I would go.

219
00:21:17,770 --> 00:21:19,740
Where is it? Why do you want to go with him?

220
00:21:19,740 --> 00:21:23,660
How much do you know about him?  What would you do if he is  a bad person.

221
00:21:23,660 --> 00:21:26,100
What's up with you all of a sudden?

222
00:21:27,460 --> 00:21:28,710
He's not a bad person!

223
00:21:28,710 --> 00:21:31,320
How could you know that?

224
00:21:31,320 --> 00:21:36,070
Why are you yelling at her?  Don't talk so loud in the house

225
00:21:38,550 --> 00:21:41,890
Please be careful around him, alright?

226
00:21:41,890 --> 00:21:44,070
Alright...

227
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:55,800
What's wrong with her all of  a sudden?  Are you seeing a man?

228
00:21:55,890 --> 00:21:58,280
At the least hint of a man...

229
00:21:58,280 --> 00:22:01,780
You know I can't ask.

230
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:28,500
How did you know? That I take lessons here.  You never once asked.

231
00:22:28,530 --> 00:22:31,270
I asked someone to find out.

232
00:22:32,330 --> 00:22:34,620
I hate flowers.

233
00:22:34,620 --> 00:22:36,710
I do, too.

234
00:22:56,770 --> 00:23:01,460
I went to the hospital which you recommended.

235
00:23:01,460 --> 00:23:04,040
You're good. Good job.

236
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:07,750
Can i go to practice?

237
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:11,540
I don't care if it's not first violin.

238
00:23:11,540 --> 00:23:14,790
I'll play any position.

239
00:23:14,790 --> 00:23:16,910
You can't.

240
00:23:16,910 --> 00:23:19,950
You aren't playing in this concert.  Why are you so stubborn?

241
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:26,210
It's your first concert as a permanent conductor.  I really  want to be there.

242
00:23:26,210 --> 00:23:28,050
Is that the only reason?

243
00:23:28,050 --> 00:23:31,340
Don't ask. That's important to me.

244
00:23:31,340 --> 00:23:35,250
If you promise to accept treatment until the end.

245
00:23:35,250 --> 00:23:37,610
I'll receive it well.

246
00:23:42,470 --> 00:23:46,700
I was very worried. I thought you were very angry.

247
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:51,450
That day I ... I thought you were treating me like a murderer.

248
00:23:51,450 --> 00:23:54,330
I was more sad than angry.

249
00:23:54,330 --> 00:23:57,430
For a year you have suspected me.

250
00:23:57,430 --> 00:24:00,250
You did not ask me even once, even though I saw you going somewhere,

251
00:24:00,250 --> 00:24:03,590
you didn't go to the after party, so where did you go?

252
00:24:03,590 --> 00:24:07,650
Relax your expression because I'm not blaming you.  Aren't you curious about anything else?

253
00:24:07,650 --> 00:24:12,500
Is there anything else you want to ask?  If there is, ask.  I'll answer anything.

254
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:16,870
I'm not at all curious. There isn't anything more.

255
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:20,570
What is it?

256
00:24:20,570 --> 00:24:25,360
Actually, there was something strange which crossed my mind.

257
00:24:26,930 --> 00:24:28,660
Something strange?

258
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:36,300
Did you perhaps know that Kim Ian, who is dead, had a brother?

259
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:49,140
Hey!

260
00:24:51,780 --> 00:24:55,750
You're late. I've been waiting a long time.

261
00:24:55,750 --> 00:24:58,760
You were waiting for me?

262
00:25:07,730 --> 00:25:11,590
Just, well, even if I wasn't feeling so good,

263
00:25:12,490 --> 00:25:14,910
do you want to hang out with me?

264
00:25:26,390 --> 00:25:32,480
♫ Even if I were nervous, now it's all disappeared. ♫

265
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:36,840
♫ It's not a dream of a moment ♫

266
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:39,670
♫ I’m in love, I’m in love ♫

267
00:25:39,670 --> 00:25:42,830
♫ t's fortunate you are here. ♫

268
00:25:42,830 --> 00:25:47,570
♫ Stay with me I hear your voice. ♫

269
00:25:47,570 --> 00:25:53,850
♫ Even if I were nervous, now it's all disappeared.  ♫

270
00:25:53,850 --> 00:25:58,360
♫ It's not a dream of a moment ♫

271
00:25:58,360 --> 00:26:01,200
♫ I’m in love, I’m in love ♫

272
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:05,140
♫ It's fortunate you are here ♫

273
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:15,400
- Good.
- Good.

274
00:26:16,430 --> 00:26:17,890
Why are you following me?

275
00:26:19,420 --> 00:26:21,370
Why after?

276
00:26:21,370 --> 00:26:23,810
Let's keep going!

277
00:26:42,260 --> 00:26:47,890
Actually, I had a lot of questions I wanted to ask today,

278
00:26:48,710 --> 00:26:52,130
but I couldn't ask you.

279
00:26:52,130 --> 00:26:56,900
Spending a summer night together was really nice.

280
00:27:06,830 --> 00:27:09,290
Unknown Caller

281
00:27:09,290 --> 00:27:12,110
They called again. That same number.

282
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:18,030
Who the hell are you?

283
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:20,930
Hello?

284
00:27:20,930 --> 00:27:24,020
♫ Goodbye, yellow brick road ♫

285
00:27:24,020 --> 00:27:28,020
♫ Where the dogs of society howl ♫

286
00:27:28,020 --> 00:27:31,370
Hello? Who is it? Why are you call—?

287
00:27:42,460 --> 00:27:47,300
♫ Oh, I've finally decided my future lies ♫

288
